Net library used to implement the mediator pattern, which is great fit for the sequence design pattern.

5
00:00:20,750 --> 00:00:27,500
It allows to send commands and queries to the appropriate handlers without coupling the sender to the

6
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:28,220
receiver.

7
00:00:29,150 --> 00:00:30,020
In mediator.

8
00:00:30,020 --> 00:00:32,299
We have a I request interface.

9
00:00:32,299 --> 00:00:36,350
So both commands and queries are modeled as a message.

10
00:00:36,350 --> 00:00:43,100
The I request interface is used to define a request which can be either a command or query.

11
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:48,080
The return type of the request can be specified as a generic parameter.

12
00:00:48,470 --> 00:00:54,980
After the I request interface definition, we should define the handlers for each command and query.

13
00:00:54,980 --> 00:01:02,000
We define a handler that inherits from the I request handler, t request, and t response, where the

14
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:07,400
t request is the type of the command or query, and t response is return type.

15
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:12,320
So we can define custom I command and I query abstraction.

16
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:19,070
So in order to make the distinction between the commands and the queries clearer, we can define two

17
00:01:19,070 --> 00:01:20,480
custom interfaces.

18
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:22,880
These are the I command and I query.

19
00:01:22,910 --> 00:01:28,130
Both interfaces can inherit from the mediators I request object.

20
00:01:30,350 --> 00:01:38,660
So in ASP.Net core application, using the mediator controllers or minimal APIs act as a entry point

21
00:01:38,660 --> 00:01:40,670
for handling Http requests.

22
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:46,730
You can see in here Http request comes from the client and the mediator acts as an entry point.

23
00:01:46,730 --> 00:01:54,320
So instead of the implementing the business logic directly within the API action, these actions delegate

24
00:01:54,320 --> 00:02:00,410
the responsibility to mediator, and after that mediator sending the command and queries.

25
00:02:00,410 --> 00:02:08,479
When a controller or minimal API receives a request, it creates a command or query object and send

26
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:09,500
