34
00:02:40,790 --> 00:02:43,820
These are known as a cross-cutting concerns.

35
00:02:44,270 --> 00:02:51,080
Mediator provides a mediator pipeline where these cross-cutting concerns can be inserted transparently.

36
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:57,680
These pipeline coordinates the request handling, ensuring that all the necessary steps are executed

37
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,940
in the right order.

38
00:02:59,090 --> 00:03:05,630
So in mediator, we have a pipeline behavior and pipeline behaviors are used to implement cross-cutting

39
00:03:05,630 --> 00:03:06,290
concerns.

40
00:03:06,290 --> 00:03:08,240
You can see the image on the slide.

41
00:03:08,270 --> 00:03:16,880
They wrap around the request handling allowing you to execute the logic before and after actual handler

42
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:17,600
is called.

43
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:25,280
So this is the mediator pipeline process before handle the actual operation mediator allowing to preprocessor

44
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:32,090
behavior or post-processor behaviors that you can use these behavior as a implementing cross-cutting

45
00:03:32,090 --> 00:03:32,840
concerns.

46
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:37,430
Here you can see the issue of microservices.

47
00:03:37,430 --> 00:03:41,990
It is also used for the implementing various cross-cutting concerns.

48
00:03:41,990 --> 00:03:44,240
The first one is log behavior.

49
00:03:44,570 --> 00:03:48,290
A behavior that logs details about the handling request.

50
00:03:48,290 --> 00:03:50,690
And the second one is the validation behavior.

51
00:03:50,690 --> 00:03:55,370
This is the behavior that validates incoming requests before they reach the handler.

52
00:03:55,370 --> 00:04:00,050
So we will use these two behaviors when implementing our issue of microservices.

53
00:04:00,050 --> 00:04:06,530
And these behaviors ensures every request processed by the mediator in the application is logged and

54
00:04:06,530 --> 00:04:12,710
validated consistently, and it demonstrates how the cross-cutting concerns can be efficiently managed

55
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:17,000
using the mediator pattern and mediator library pipeline behaviors.

56
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:24,380
So we can say that using mediator in ASP.Net applications provides a structured and clean way to handle

57
00:04:24,380 --> 00:04:25,970
